cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about unsupervised learning for video analysis, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes two unsupervised learning layers that can be added to regular neural network layers for extracting slow and fast changing features at different depths. This suggests that the paper could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper provides both a closed-form solution and an online learning algorithm for the proposed layers, which suggests that it could also fall under neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
